  "prompt": "What are the penalties for money laundering under federal law?",
  "response": "Under federal law, money laundering can result in significant criminal penalties, including:\n\n1. Potential prison sentences:\n- Up to 10-20 years in federal prison per offense\n- Maximum sentences can increase for more serious cases\n\n2. Financial penalties:\n- Substantial fines, potentially hundreds of thousands or millions of dollars\n- Forfeitures of assets obtained through illegal activities\n\n3. Additional potential consequences:\n- Asset seizure\n- Criminal record\n- Loss of professional licenses\n- Potential civil penalties\n\nThe specific penalties depend on factors like transaction amount, criminal history, and specific circumstances of the offense. Federal agencies like the Department of Justice prosecute money laundering cases under statutes such as the Bank Secrecy Act and Money Laundering Control Act.",
